The paper discusses unsupervised methods for identifying phrases and subphrase structures in natural language without using any prior linguistic knowledge. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL), which are all relevant to natural language processing and text mining.
